# M-One Solution API — Laravel + Filament CMS

Build a production-ready Laravel 12 backend with Filament v3 admin panel and a RESTful JSON API. The existing fresh-install Laravel project at `d:\GitHub\m-one-solution-api` will be the target. No Filament or CMS packages are installed yet.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Driver**: The [.env](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/.env) currently uses **SQLite** (local dev). For production (cPanel), this should be switched to **MySQL**. The migrations are written to be DB-agnostic but please confirm whether this project is being developed locally with SQLite or already targeting MySQL now.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Image Storage**: `spatie/laravel-medialibrary` will store uploaded images to `storage/app/public`. For production on cPanel, a symlink `public/storage` → `storage/app/public` must be created (`php artisan storage:link`). If the plan is to use a cloud CDN (Cloudflare R2, S3, etc.), please let me know and we can configure it accordingly.

> [!NOTE]
> **Filament Admin URL**: The Filament panel will be accessible at `/admin`. The default admin guard is used. A seeder will create the first Super Admin user.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1 — Package Dependencies

Install via `composer require`:

| Package | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `filament/filament:^3.0` | Admin Panel CMS |
| `spatie/laravel-medialibrary:^11.0` | File/image uploads with WebP conversion |
| `spatie/laravel-permission:^6.0` | RBAC (roles & permissions) |

#### [MODIFY] [composer.json](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/composer.json)
Add the three packages above to `require`.

---

### Phase 2 — Configuration & Security

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/.env)
- `APP_NAME=M-One Solution API`
- `CACHE_STORE=file` (switch from database to file cache for simplicity; can upgrade to Redis later)
- `FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000` (overridden in production to `https://m-one-solution.com`)

#### [MODIFY] [config/cors.php](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/config/cors.php)
- `allowed_origins` → read from `env('FRONTEND_URL')` — restricts API access to the Next.js frontend only.

---

### Phase 3 — Models & Migrations

Nine new migrations + Eloquent models (all with `SoftDeletes` where appropriate):

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_categories_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `name`, `slug` (unique), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_posts_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `title`, `slug` (unique), `excerpt` (text), `content` (longText), `category_id` (FK, nullable), `author_id` (FK to users), `published_at` (timestamp, nullable), `timestamps`, `softDeletes`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_services_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `title`, `slug` (unique), `category` (string), `short_description` (text), `full_description` (longText), `features` (JSON), `benefits` (JSON), `keywords` (JSON), `order_column` (int), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_projects_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `title`, `slug`, `category` (string), `description` (text), `client_name` (nullable), `project_url` (nullable), `is_featured` (boolean, default false), `order_column` (int), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_team_members_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `name`, `role`, `social_linkedin` (nullable), `social_github` (nullable), `social_instagram` (nullable), `order_column` (int), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_alumnis_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `name`, `school`, `batch_period` (string), `order_column` (int), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_testimonials_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `name`, `role`, `company`, `content` (text), `rating` (int 1-5), `is_active` (boolean, default true), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_partners_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `name`, `order_column` (int), `timestamps`

#### [NEW] `database/migrations/…_create_settings_table.php`
Fields: `id`, `key` (string, unique), `value` (text, nullable), `timestamps`

**Models** (one per entity, in `app/Models/`): `Category`, `Post`, `Service`, `Project`, `TeamMember`, `Alumni`, `Testimonial`, `Partner`, `Setting`

All image-bearing models (`Post`, `Service`, `Project`, `TeamMember`, `Alumni`, `Testimonial`, `Partner`) implement `HasMedia` / `InteractsWithMedia` from Spatie MediaLibrary.

---

### Phase 4 — Filament Admin Resources

Filament v3 Resources are generated in `app/Filament/Resources/`. Each resource provides full CRUD forms + list tables.

| Resource | Notable Fields |
|---|---|
| `CategoryResource` | name, slug (auto-generated) |
| `PostResource` | title, slug, category (select), rich text content, image upload, published_at (date picker), author (auto-set to current user) |
| `ServiceResource` | title, slug, category, descriptions, features/benefits/keywords (repeater fields), image |
| `ProjectResource` | title, category, description, client, URL, is_featured toggle, image |
| `TeamMemberResource` | name, role, socials, image, drag-sortable order |
| `AlumniResource` | name, school, batch_period (select/text), image |
| `TestimonialResource` | name, role, company, content, rating (star select 1-5), is_active toggle, image |
| `PartnerResource` | name, logo image upload, drag-sortable order |
| `SettingResource` | key-value pairs (custom page, not a standard resource) |

**RBAC via Spatie Permission**:
- Role `super_admin`: access to all resources + Settings page
- Role `editor`: access to Post, Service, Project, TeamMember, Alumni, Testimonial, Partner only

Each resource's `canAccess()` / `canCreate()` etc. guards will check role.

---

### Phase 5 — REST API Endpoints

#### [NEW] [routes/api.php](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/routes/api.php)

All routes are public (read-only GET), protected only by CORS and rate limiting:

```
GET /api/posts              → PostController@index   (paginated, published only)
GET /api/posts/{slug}       → PostController@show
GET /api/services           → ServiceController@index
GET /api/services/{slug}    → ServiceController@show
GET /api/projects           → ProjectController@index  (?featured=true filter)
GET /api/team               → TeamController@index
GET /api/alumni             → AlumniController@index   (grouped by batch_period)
GET /api/testimonials       → TestimonialController@index  (is_active=true only)
GET /api/partners           → PartnerController@index
GET /api/settings           → SettingController@index  (returns {key: value} map)
```

**API Resource transformers** (`app/Http/Resources/`): One resource class per entity to shape the JSON response and include media URLs.

**Cache strategy** (file cache):
- Each endpoint result is cached with a tag like `cache()->remember('posts.index', 3600, fn() => ...)`
- A model `Observer` or `saved`/`deleted` event hook calls `Cache::forget(...)` to auto-bust cache on admin save.

---

### Phase 6 — Security & Hardening

#### [MODIFY] [app/Http/Middleware/…](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/app/Http)
- **CORS**: `config/cors.php` — `allowed_origins` restricted to `FRONTEND_URL`
- **Rate Limiting**: In `bootstrap/app.php`, define a `api` throttle limit of 60 requests/minute per IP
- **JSON-only**: Register a global middleware on `/api/*` to force `Accept: application/json` — this ensures Laravel returns JSON 422/404/500 instead of HTML

**Standardized error response** via `bootstrap/app.php` exception handler:
```json
{"success": false, "message": "...", "errors": {...}}
```

---

### Phase 7 — Seeders

#### [MODIFY] [database/seeders/DatabaseSeeder.php](file:///d:/GitHub/m-one-solution-api/database/seeders/DatabaseSeeder.php)
- Create Spatie roles: `super_admin`, `editor`
- Create first admin user: `admin@m-one-solution.com` / password: `password` (changeable)
- Assign `super_admin` role
- Optionally: 3–5 dummy posts, 2 services, 2 projects via factories

