## Verification Plan

### API Tests (Terminal)
After `php artisan migrate --seed`, run:

```bash
# Confirm all routes are registered
php artisan route:list --path=api

# Test a GET endpoint (requires php artisan serve running)
curl http://localhost:8000/api/posts
curl http://localhost:8000/api/settings
```

Expected: `200 OK` with `{"data": [...], "links": {...}, "meta": {...}}` JSON.

### Manual Verification (Browser)
1. Start local server: `php artisan serve`
2. Open `http://localhost:8000/admin` → should redirect to Filament login
3. Log in with `admin@m-one-solution.com` / `password`
4. Navigate through all Resources and confirm forms load
5. Create one Blog Post, one Service — confirm they appear
6. Open `http://localhost:8000/api/posts` in browser — confirm the new post is in the JSON response
7. Open `http://localhost:8000/api/settings` — confirm settings key-value map returns

### Automated Tests
```bash
php artisan test
```
Existing default tests should still pass. New feature tests will be added for API endpoints.
